          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726064867616-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726064867616-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1726064867616-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle, then whisk your <strong>egg[s]</strong>, 35g <span class=\"text-purple\">[50g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[70g]</span><strong> flour</strong>, 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>in a jug, then place in the fridge to rest – this is your<strong> batter</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces, then add them to a separate pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 22-25 min, then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726064873612-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726064873612-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726064873612-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726064873612-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1726064873612-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained potatoes</strong> to one side of a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray<strong> </strong>with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min</p><p>Fill 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>holes per person of a <strong>muffin tray</strong> with a very small drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>(about 1 tsp per hole) and put it in the oven for 8 min to heat up</p><p>Tip: No muffin tray? Fill a small oven-proof dish with a generous drizzle of vegetable oil to make one giant Yorkshire!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1726064883366-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1726064883366-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1726064883366-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1726064883366-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1726064883366-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After 8 min, remove the muffin tray from the oven and evenly drizzle the <strong>rested</strong> <strong>batter</strong> into the hot oil</p><p>Return the tray to the oven for 20 min until puffed up and golden – these are your <strong>Yorkshire puddings</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>carrot[s]</strong> to a low heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>carrot mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1726064887488-x200.jpg",
