            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes have had an initial 15 min, remove the tray from the oven and add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to the other side of the baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 18-20 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are golden and crispy – these are your <strong>roasties</strong></p><p>While the chicken is cooking, crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skin[s]</p>",
